This is M.M. Pickthall's English rendering of the Qur'an. It is
technically not in the public domain in the US, because it was published
in India after 1922. However, Pickthall died in 1936, so it is now in
the public domain in countries with the death+50 public domain rule
(e.g. Australia, Pakistan, Canada), and it is also in the public domain
in countries with the death+70 rule (e.g. UK and countries in the
European Union), as of the end of 2006.

